Class GymManager

java.lang.Object
models.GymManager
public class GymManager
extends java.lang.Object
The GymManager class is the user interface class that processes the command line inputs and prints the corresponding outputs.

    • handleAddMember

      private boolean handleAddMember​(java.lang.String command, Plans membershipType)
      Handles inputs with command type A, AF, AP Parses command for member information Checks if member is valid and if so, adds member to member database
      Parameters:
      command - Entire line of instruction containing member information
      membershipType - Standard, Family, or Premium plan of member
      Returns:
      true if member successfully added, false otherwise

    • handleCheckIn

      private void handleCheckIn​(java.lang.String command, boolean isGuest)
      Handles inputs with command C and CG Parses command for fitness class and member information Checks in the member if 1. The member is in the database 2. Their membership is not expired, their 3. Their date of birth is valid 4. The specified class exists 5. The class has no time conflict with the member's other fitness clases 6. The member is not already checked in Displays appropriate error messages if unable to check in member to class
      Parameters:
      command - Entire line of instruction containing member and class information
      isGuest - true if checking in guest, false otherwise

    • handleDropClass

      private void handleDropClass​(java.lang.String command, boolean isGuest)
      Handles inputs with command D and DG Parses command for fitness class and member information Drops the member from the class if 1. The member is initially checked into the class 2. Their date of birth is valid 3. The specified class exists Displays appropriate error messages if unable to drop member from class
      Parameters:
      command - Entire line of instruction containing member and class information
      isGuest - true of dropping class for guest, false otherwise

    • handleCancelMembership

      Parameters:
      command - Entire line of instruction containing member information
      Returns:
      true if membership cancel success, false otherwise
